The equilibrium binding of neonicotinoids with Ls-AChBP was determined by quenching of intrinsic tryptophan fluorescence. Ls-AChBP at 600 nM in binding site concentration in 20 mM Tris–HCl buffer with 0.02% NaN3 (pH 8.0) was incubated with each ligand at various concentrations on a 96-well plate. Ls-AChBP was excited at 280 nm, and emission intensity was recorded at 342 nm using Varioskan microplate reader (Thermo Fisher Scientific) at room temperature. Data were fitted by non-linear regression according to the following equation using Prism Software version 4.03 (GraphPad Software): \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
